       <div id="comment_859898" class="comment">I owned a diesel Rabbit in the '70's.  I liked it, and at the time diesel was cheaper than gas.  Fitted with 2 tanks I could drive down to Mexico to fill-up.  I think I averaged around 30-35 mpg.<br /><br />Fast forward to 2006 when I bought a Prius.  Back seats down I could carry a 27 speed bike and camping equipment for 2 for a couple of months on the road.  The Prius, now with 60,000 miles averages around 48 mpg.<br /><br />However, if Ford could get that ECOnetic into the States, I probably would consider trading in the Prius.  If and if I could carry the same stuff I could get into the Prius.</div>
